rComments: She is by far the worst teacher I had in my university career so far. She's very monotone, her midterms make no sense. She talks to fast and has a few words in every powerpoint because she's reading a script. If you can find another sociology teacher do it! Be sure to be ready to do lots of homework.
Horrible Prof. Tough grader. If you get the chance to take another class do it. I regret taking this class.
You need to read everything in the textbook because the lectures are not very informative. Very hard to take notes during the lecture.
She talks very slow, I really didn't enjoy listening to her lectures, the slides were also unorganized. The last paper was long and not fun

If you have the chance to take another professor for this class, do it! Her lectures aren't engaging, and I had to watch them outside of class because she moved so fast. The textbook readings are also very long, and she didn't allow much time to read them between classes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: If you don't like being stressed out, don't take her class. We had a major assignment almost every week on a new computer program that we were given little to no instruction on how to use or download. We weren't tested on major concepts, but little details from the textbook, so the tests were really hard if you don't have a great memory.
Not an enjoyable class and although Professore Lieflander is caring outside of academics, she is not a good professor.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Gives good feedback', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Do not take her because the tests were hard and I was barely graded for my final essay which is not fair
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Ok guys here's the tricks to excelling with her teaching style! - listen to every lecture in 1.5x speed once uploaded after class (DO IT) - her theories are only taught verbally! I can't stress this enough! She speaks the information you need to know and has a minimal slideshow - you need to know 2 chapters of material every week (ALOT)

A common sociology prof for most soc basics. When you have her, be strapped in and ready for it. Lectures are dry and slow so listen to them afterwards at 1.5x speed but this is one class that you NEED to know what's happening. Assignments come quick and she sticks like glue to her rubric, every detail!(and there's a lot of em) Avoid if possible!!

Riva Lieflander's classes are difficult, no two ways around it. HOWEVER, if you actually read the lecture slides before class (DENSE, skip the textbook read these) and actually do the homework (I did every odd # question in the textbook) you will at least pass if not excel. Her office hours are worth their weight in gold. she made me like stats!?!?

She made her midterms open book so the questions are very very hard. Her skeleton outline assignments were graded very harsh because i had all the information correct and the outline was a bit off and i only got a 60%... I wouldnt take this class again it made me hate sociology

The lectures feel as if she is reading out of a book. The PowerPoints are not helpful and there's a lot of material for just one semester. Also, this is the only online class I've had where a prof has no webcam on, no chat and minimal interactions going . I will admit, she is present for students when they have questions so that's a strength.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: The lectures drove me absolutely insane. She will put one word, or sometimes one sentence (if you're lucky) up on a slide, and then actually flesh out the concepts super fast vocally and expect you to be able to take all those notes down. Before you can even stop to try to understand, she's onto the next topic. Dreaded the lectures every week.

Really hard class. Talked to her quite often during office hours and was told I was always going in the right direction but my marks tell me otherwise. I would not take this class unless you like math and a lot of homework.
Listen to me. DO NOT TAKE HER CLASS. The course structure is in absolute shambles. Way too much content to learn for an intro sociology class.

I am writing this bad review because she deserves it. She barely responds toany emails, she doesn't allow her students to interrupt for questions. She gave lectures late and sound likeascript and posted 9 lectures 6 days before the midtermShe gave looong questions in the midterm with a total of 60 questions. She expects the class to do mediocrely.

I get COVID is tough but this prof posted 9 lectures less than a week before our midterm and claimed that it is our job to catch up and be prepared. She still neglects her job to teach us, stood us up during a zoom lecture, doesn't explain assignments, and she's just plain rude to her students. She loves screwing us over & playing the victim.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I'm writing this in response to COVID season. She cares. She will listen. She will make changes. She knows how to teach. Is she aware of students' situations? Completely aloof. Does she know how to structure her course? Absolutely not. Lectures consistent of reading very fast off a script, no questions, not chat. Not enough words to explain here

Her lectures may be a bit boring, but she is super responsive and really willing to help. She basically teaches you every single bits in your assignments, she provides assignment lab outside of classes. You can even expect 10mins response during the weekends. I never had a more passionate prof than her, shes my favourite prof among all.

Oufff for an elective, it took up way too much time. She is definitely very passionate about what she teaches though her lectures are boring. She requires us to know her slides and on top of that the material from 2 other textbooks. If you love sociology, maybe you'll love her. I just needed it for my program and would never take it again...

this class is relatively easy if you actually go to class. Rica offers tons of support and helpful tips. She basically gives you the answers to all the tests in her lectures. However if you dont stay up to date on lectures youll fall behind and get lost as everything is connected
The textbook has more knowledge and is more interesting as a prof and she smells like old books.

Riva is a very nice professor and cares about her students. However, both tests in this class were extremely difficult and large homework assignments every week. Expectations are unclear and grading seems to be unpredictable. Lectures are hard to follow. Riva is a good person but I wouldn't take her class again.

Alright. I am not one to write reviews, but this is despicable. Students need to be careful with displacing hard course material/too much difficult material on a professor themselves. Riva Lieflander extends FAR beyond her office hours for support - if you give a damn, she gives a damn. Doesn't mean you will do well, and I agree this course (...)
I hate it, that's all I can say

This class has changed my life completely, even with hours and hours of working/studying/frustration on this class, somehow it still managed to ruined my CGPA, my application for Master, and my life. Literally, most memorable prof ever

The first midterm is all about prerequisite class's stuff. Which is NOT fair for those who didn't take the prerequisite class with her/with different profs, but again, she doesn't care. So either take both classes with her, or don't take any at all.

RIva is very nice and means well although the course is very tough and difficult if you do not have a strong understanding on quantitative analysis. The assignments are very intense and take a lot of time. The main issue was information overload. If you took the communication equivalent for 3rd year this course will most likely be very hard.

Everyday struggling on the assignments and you won't get a good marks on that, that's how hopeless it is. For a fourth year student who is graduating soon, this class basically tells you to jump off the building.
Avoid!!!!!!!!! She is a nice professor, but she is a tough grader. You will not get a good grade unless you are genius (by good grade I mean 60%)
Seriously, this prof doesn't understand that most students in this class are NOT in math/static major, so just, RUN WHILE YOU CAN! Don't risk your GPA.

Riva is one of the worst profs I have had in university. She spends half the class telling personal stories that do not relate to the class. The expectations on assignments are unclear making it hard to get good grades on the assignments.

She explains the concepts fairly well and gives a lot of helpful tips on how to do well on assignments and tests. There is a lot of work though so don't fall behind. Overall, I had a decent experience with this professor.

You can tell she genuinely loves stats & is passionate about it. She tries to be funny &ease the mood with her personality, which is nice. She will give you long & difficult online assignments every week. Definitely buy the textbook because her lectures are filled with information &are really confusing. Makes everything due back to back. Terrible!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: If you are not good at math, you will not pass. The assignments and weekly tests are incredibly time consuming. It took me approximately 6-8 hours to complete weekly assignments worth 1% each. She repeats over and over again that the content of the course is "very easy" when it is incredibly difficult. Avoid if you can.

I love her. I had her in a social research methods class, which is a very boring subject, so the lectured were a bit dry. She gives lots of little assignments, which I really loved because it give more opportunity to get your grades up. She is also just a total angel. So kind and helpful whenever you need her. really goes above and beyond.

Riva is a total sweetheart. She tends to stress out about the quality of her classes and the lectures can be a little dry, but you learn a lot and it's an easy A if you do the work. The first half of the term was definitely harder. Overall, a good prof who cares about her work and her students.

Do not take Riva's class. She is a nice woman, but she cannot teach properly. She over explains material and burns through it way too quickly. Many students in stats aren't amazing at math, but she barely explains the math and does not allow calculators. We had to memorize equations for the midterm and that was the reason I failed it. Avoid

Riva is a truly amazing professor. I've never had someone care so deeply about both her subject and her students before. Even though I found statistics challenging, the prof was so encouraging and so available for help that it made it feel surmountable. Riva truly sets you up for success, her slides are clear and helpful, tests are fair.

Riva is a great math teacher. But thats it. If you have no knowledge of math she will basically make you feel useless cuz she assumes you already know how to do math. Considering she teaches mostly sociology students, she was left with a class full of confused students. I passed the class cuz I taught myself the material. Avoid.
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Accessible outside class', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Just don't take Riva's class. If you value yourself and your mental stability please avoid her. She teaches way too fast and does burns through material, overly complicated material, and does not explain the math concepts behind statistics whatsoever. A V O I D

Riva is a nice person no doubt, however she fails to connect with student as a group and individually. Majority of students who take her 3142 and 4117 classes are required to take the courses and thus most often have little to no mathematic abilities further than the highschool level. Her material is not presented at the introductory level needed.

Riva is fantastic! She cares about her students, she runs office hours all of the time and is always there to help in any way she can. She is really passionate about what she does and it really comes through in her teaching! I would definitely take a class with her again :)

Worst teacher I have ever had. And I have two BA's. I've had many teachers. This one is a total disaster. No details as to what he expects for assignments. Zero ability to explain the concepts he is trying to teach. I leave each class understanding less, with more questions, and in doubt as to what I have "learned" so far. Avoid. Avoid. Avoid!!

Riva is a wonderful prof, but makes the course really heavy, with ridiculously time consuming assignments. She does put in so much work to help her students though, and truly wants you to succeed. The midterm was hard but the final was fair. If you put the work in and take advantage of her giving the option for so much extra help you'll do fine.
Riva is so sweet and kind hearted, she is always there for her students. Very clear in what she is teaching and always wants us to ask questions if we're lost. Thank you Riva! You're the best!

Riva made this class bearable. Mathematics  not a strong suit but the class is mandatory and she does try her very best to make it at least somewhat enjoyable. She truly does want her students to do well and I appreciated her efforts to do well by us. Do the weekly chapters (I know, I know but still) and you will do fine.

The prof is nice but unclear and lectures move way too fast w/too much info. It is by far the worst class I have ever been in. I still can't believe how unnecessarily difficult it is, especially considering a lot of students haven't taken math since high school. Despite trying my best I will probably fail for the first time in my uni career. AVOID.

For a stats class, she tried her best to make it interesting. Read the assigned chapters ahead of lectures, you'll be lost otherwise. If you follow the assignment instructions it's easy to do well. Prepare for the exams and do the readings and you'll be fine. She was always quick to reply to questions, and very thorough if you had problems.

Lovely woman with a great sense of humour. Passionate about statistical analysis, however, sometimes she isn't very clear. If you haven't read the text book before class, good luck following the lecture. Though, her slides are quite detailed and uploaded to black board ahead of time which is great! For a mandatory course, it wasn't too bad.

Okay, so here's the thing. Riva Lieflander is a sweet heart and will do absolutely everything she can for her students. But she also makes them uncomfortable. She discusses her abusive father every class. Her lectures are boring. Midterm was very easy, then she made the final insanely hard.

At first I was shocked that I only got a B- as I normally ace my classes, especially ones that heavily based on tests. I actually worked harder and did more readings than the other half of the credit, where I got an A. I found out after that everyone's marks where horrible. Getting a B- from that class was a feat itself, apparently. Don't do it.

Prof Lieflander was a nice lady who tried to be as clear as possible in her lectures.  Good thing was she always uploaded her slides online before lecture and you could skip that class without your grades affected! Just do all the readings on her custom textbook and memorize all the dates, facts and stats, you'll be assured a 90+ in this course!
She was terrible

She snaked on the final exam. Midterm was straight forward: read the textbook and you're good. Final exam she threw in statistics like what was the divorce rate in hamilton from 1995-1999. Neolithic era, Palaeolithic era.. what? Aside from the exam she is really boring and reveals too much personal info. Would avoid at all costs.

She made the final exam in a completely different format from midterm. Half of the final exam was full of unimportant stats and years instead of important sociological concepts, which we were NOT expecting at all. Plus her lectures were boring and she used SO much personal examples saying they r relevant. LOL NO THEY R NOT.

Talks TOO MUCH about her personal life. Very much boring and scares the students. If you have her as a prof, don't bother going to classes, just read the textbook (since everything on the slides is a copy and paste from the textbook). Her slides have TOO MUCH WORDS too!!!

Have no idea why she is replacing the previous professor at University of Toronto for this course. She requires TOO MUCH from you and talks about her personal life TOO MUCH. Her lectures are SO boring though I do not hate her personally, but I do not think she is a perfect professor.
Avoid taking classes with her if you can! She's a really tough grader! Also the exam is cumulative and her slides are way too long. She also expects too much from her students
She is a really tough marker! Even though her instructions and expectations are clear, she's really tough on the grading

Overall, she's not a bad professor. But I took the course in summer school and she expected the whole 2nd year class to finish a 12-15 page research essay in two weeks, despite everyone complaining. On top of that, she spends most time in class talking about her personal life experience which can be very uncomfortable (and shocking) to listen to.

Lieflander is a prof that you won't forget. She means well, but comes off too personal and often felt uncomfortable with her overload of information about herself. Many unnecessary and long assignments that are hardly worth anything. Class is a breeze if you read the book. Just could not get over her TMI, often had nothing to do with the material.

overall a good prof. she tends to talk about herself a little too much. assignments take a lot and i mean ALOT of time doing. and some are only worth 3%.....avoid if you don't want to read a lot of the textbook and secondary textbooks.

This teacher is very passionate about sociology and will do everything she can to help you. She's an absolute sweetheart but she does expect a lot in terms of time that you have to put into the work but shes very clear about what  she expects and midterms and finals are more than fair and you know what to expect going in.

This prof is a really nice person, however the work load is FAR greater then it needs to be. She shares a lot of personal matter that may come across as annoying and distracting. We had a really unprofessional TA grade our assignments. Her comments were extremely redundant and rude to say the least. Her overall grading was extremely inconsistent.
DO NOT. I repeat DO NOT take a class with her. Extremely demanding for an elective.

She is a very interesting professor, she explains everything with a  lot of detail. You can tell she has a huge passion for sociology which makes the class interesting. She is precise with what how she wants you to do your projects.She is really helpful and email you soon after you emailed her!Great prof! You will learn a lot with her :)

Riva is interesting to say the least. She goes into too much detail about her personal life to the point it becomes unprofessional. She's a little crazy but she's not a bad prof. You use the textbook quite a bit but most of the info are on her slides.

The course in itself is easy but the prof is extremely demanding. This course required more work then all my other courses combined. The prof knows what she's talking about however, she jumps from subject to subject all the time and gives way to much personal information about her own life.
